U.K. Spends Almost $1.6 Billion of Fast-Start Funds for Climate Finance

-- B y   A l e x   M o r a l e s   a n d   M a t h e w   C a r r
-- 
2011-12-06T09:51:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-06/u-k-allocates-1-billion-pounds-of-fast-start-climate-finance.html
The U.K. government said it paid out
two-thirds of its 1.5 billion pounds ($2.3 billion) of “fast-
start” finance for climate protection and adaptation by
developing nations promised for 2010 to 2012.  “We have now passed the 1 billion-pound fast-start climate
finance milestone,” Energy Secretary  Chris Huhne  said today at
United Nations climate talks in Durban, South Africa.  Britain spent 487 million pounds this year, compared with
569 million pounds last year,  according to a document  on the
website of the Department of Energy and Climate Change. It has
budgeted 2.9 billion pounds through 2015.  One program includes developing climate-change adaptation
plans, which have been endorsed for Bangladesh, Bolivia,
Cambodia,  Mozambique , Nepal, Niger, Tajikistan, Zambia, Grenada,
Jamaica, St. Vincent and the Grenadines, St. Lucia and Samoa,
according to the document.  To contact the reporters on this story:
